The Kenya Urban Roads Authority (Kura) has decried theft of street lights, road signs, guard rails and street poles despite measures to combat the crime. 
Kura Director-General Silas Kinoti said thieves have stolen items worth Sh500,000 belonging to the authority in the last few days and that such theft has increased over the past year.  



